Beth,<br><br>
I mentioned that you might want to talk to him in quiet times.  I  believe that whenever couples need to talk they both need to be calm.  You might want to arrange a time.  A Saturday lunch for example might be the place.  He might appreciate the time to think over what he wants to say to you.<br><br>
I don't know if Art or SW's wives might want to chat with you, but there experiences are first hand and no doubt invalualble.  Ask your partner, if he is still going to counseling, if you could go along as well -- or by yourself.  There is no reason for you to isolate yourself, that won't do anyone any good.  You may want to ask what you want from each other in this relationship.  All of my points should be regarded as hit and miss.  Life is hard and it is rarely fair.<br><br>
Paul<br>

